3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin calculates AAVE/USDT funding rates using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices over the 8-hour period. The exchange applies a funding rate cap of ±0.375% to prevent extreme payments during volatile periods. Funding settlements occur at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, with positions held at these times automatically charged or credited based on their direction and the prevailing rate."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AAVE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE's status as a leading DeFi lending protocol creates unique funding rate dynamics driven by governance events, protocol upgrades, and DeFi market sentiment. The token's moderate volatility and KuCoin's global user base contribute to more predictable funding patterns compared to smaller altcoins, making it suitable for systematic arbitrage approaches."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical AAVE Funding Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE funding rates on KuCoin typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% during normal market conditions, with positive rates dominating during DeFi rallies. The token shows distinct seasonal patterns around Aave governance proposals and major protocol updates, often creating 2-3 day periods of elevated positive funding. Unlike major cryptocurrencies, AAVE funding rarely sustains extreme negative rates due to limited short interest from institutional players. Historical data shows funding spikes during broader altcoin momentum, particularly when AAVE outperforms ETH on a relative basis."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between KuCoin and Binance AAVE perpetuals frequently yields 0.02-0.08% profit per 8-hour cycle due to different user bases and liquidity patterns. KuCoin's funding rates often lag Binance by 4-6 hours during trending moves, creating predictable arbitrage windows. The exchange's integration with trading bots makes automated funding rate strategies particularly effective for AAVE. Cash-and-carry arbitrage using KuCoin's spot AAVE and perpetuals can be profitable when funding rates exceed 0.1%, though spot liquidity limitations require careful position sizing."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE's correlation with broader DeFi sector movements creates basis risk when holding arbitrage positions during sector rotations or regulatory uncertainty. KuCoin's 2023 SEC charges introduced counterparty risk that must be factored into longer-term arbitrage strategies, particularly for positions held overnight. The exchange's moderate perpetual liquidity for AAVE means large arbitrage positions (>$50,000) may experience slippage during volatile periods. Funding rate calculations can become distorted during extreme volatility when the perpetual premium diverges significantly from normal ranges, potentially leading to unexpected settlement amounts."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does KuCoin settle AAVE/USDT funding rates?","answer":"KuCoin settles AAVE/USDT funding every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. You only pay or receive funding if you hold a position at these exact settlement times, making intraday trading funding-neutral."},{"question":"What's the typical funding rate range for AAVE on KuCoin?","answer":"AAVE funding rates on KuCoin typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% during normal conditions, with rates capped at ±0.375%. During DeFi rallies or governance events, positive rates can sustain for several days, creating consistent arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"Is AAVE liquidity sufficient for large funding arbitrage positions on KuCoin?","answer":"KuCoin's AAVE perpetual liquidity supports positions up to $30-50,000 without significant slippage during normal conditions. For larger arbitrage strategies, consider splitting positions across multiple settlement periods or using limit orders to minimize market impact."},{"question":"How do AAVE governance events affect funding rates on KuCoin?","answer":"Major Aave governance proposals and protocol upgrades typically drive 2-3 days of elevated positive funding rates as traders position for potential price moves. These events often create the most profitable arbitrage windows, though increased volatility requires careful risk management."}]}]
